'''敞開的門'''（{{lang-en|Open Doors}}）是一个[[非宗派教会|非宗派]]性质的[[基督教传教活动|基督教活动]]组织，旨在支持全世界内受迫害的基督徒。该组织和当地的合作伙伴共同进行[[圣经|圣经]]与基督教相关作品的分发，训练[[门徒_(基督教)|门徒]]<ref>{{cite book|last=Green|first=George W.|title=Special use vehicles: an illustrated history of unconventional cars and trucks worldwide|publisher=McFarland|year=2003|pages=151|isbn=0-7864-1245-3|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CCZcwlhyaJsC&pg=PA151&dq=open+doors+brother+andrew|accessdate=2009-04-06}}</ref>，并提供实际的支持，如紧急救助援助等。该组织的既定目标是提高人们对全球范围的迫害活动的认识，动员世界各地基督徒祈祷、支持和行动。组织总部位于荷兰[[埃尔默洛|埃尔默洛]]，是国际圣经代理商论坛的成员之一。

目前，敞开的门在世界有20个分支机构。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.opendoors.org/|title=Open Doors worldwide|publisher=opendoors.org|accessdate=2020-09-19|archive-date=2021-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210320214138/https://www.opendoors.org/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

== 历史 ==
敞开的门由荷兰人安得烈·范德比爾（Andrew van der Bijl）在1955年创立，他被广泛称作安得烈弟兄。当时他决定走私圣经到排斥基督徒的共产主义波兰，<ref>{{cite book|last=Hertzke|first=Allen D.|title=Freeing God's children|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield|year=2004|isbn=0-7425-0804-8|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oEBROQZMCo0C&pg=PA401|accessdate=2009-04-06|archive-date=2020-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200614161719/https://books.google.com/books?id=oEBROQZMCo0C&pg=PA401|dead-url=no}}</ref>后来他又继续把圣经走私到许多被苏联控制的国家，1957年他获得了一辆蓝色[[大众甲壳虫|大众甲壳虫]]，用于运送工作。<ref>{{cite book|last=Desmond|first=Kevin|title=The Least Likely: If God Can Use Them, He Can Use You!|publisher=Kregel Publications|year=2005|page=113|isbn=0-8254-6061-1|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=a_BavuACGbkC&pg=PA113|accessdate=2009-04-07|archive-date=2020-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200614161626/https://books.google.com/books?id=a_BavuACGbkC&pg=PA113|dead-url=no}}</ref>随后，敞开的门的工作不断扩展，将网络扩大到整个东欧和苏联。

1981年6月18日，敞开的门在夜间向中国南方城市[[汕头市|汕头市]]附近的海滩运送了100万本中文圣经，该计划取名为“珍珠计划”。珍珠计划在大卫兄弟带领下，20个国际团队共同合作，一艘名为加百列的驳船携带了232个经过防水包装，重达1吨的包裹，其中共有100万本中文圣经。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.christiantoday.com/article/open.doors.project.pearl.25th.anniversary.of.delivering.1.million.bibles.to.china/6713.htm|title=Open Doors: Project Pearl - 25th Anniversary of Delivering 1 Million Bibles to China|website=Christian Today|language=en|type=Press release|access-date=2018-01-20|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308100543/https://www.christiantoday.com/article/open.doors.project.pearl.25th.anniversary.of.delivering.1.million.bibles.to.china/6713.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>一艘名为米迦勒的拖船负责将加百列拖到海滩上，拖船穿过停泊的中国海军舰船，晚上9时到达海滩，约1万名当地基督徒聚集在一起，把圣经运送到岸上，随后被送往中国各地分发。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://radiofreechina.wordpress.com/2007/05/08/brother-david-gods-smuggler-to-china-had-died-at-70-today/|title=Brother David "God's smuggler to China" had died at 70 today|last=Hattaway|first=Paul|date=2007-05-08|work=Radio Free China|access-date=2018-04-20|agency=Assist News Service|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225010407/https://radiofreechina.wordpress.com/2007/05/08/brother-david-gods-smuggler-to-china-had-died-at-70-today/|dead-url=no}}</ref> [[时代杂志|时代杂志]]将珍珠计划称作了不起的计划，是中国历史上同类项目中规模最大的一次。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,924980,00.html|title=Risky Rendezvous at Swatow|last1=Hoyle|first1=Russ|first2=Bing W|last2=Wong|date=1981-10-19|work=[[Time_(magazine)|TIME]]|accessdate=2009-04-07|archive-date=2013-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130826021650/http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,924980,00.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref><span id="Project Pearl"></span>

1988年，敞开的门利用[[开放政策|开放政策]]<ref name=":0">{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1988-08-06/local/me-6951_1_santa-ana|title=Local News in Brief: Santa Ana Group to Legally Ship Million Bibles to Russia|date=1988-08-06|work=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=2009-04-07|page=2|issn=0458-3035}}</ref>作为机会，向[[俄罗斯正教会|俄罗斯东正教教会]]提供了100万本俄语圣经，费用为250万美元。<ref>{{cite news|title=OC charity to ship first load of Bibles to Soviets by Dec. 25|last=Brodeur|first=Nicole|work={{tsl|en|Orange County Register||Orange County Register}}|date=1988-10-15|page=b.08|issn=0886-4934|id={{ProQuest|272237755}}}} (Registration required)</ref>通过与联合圣经协会合作，仅用1年多时间就完成了此次任务。<ref>{{cite news|title=County-based ministry has sent 1 million Bibles to Christians in USSR|last=Owen|first=Mary|work={{tsl|en|Orange County Register||Orange County Register}}|date=1989-12-30|issn=0886-4934|page=E.05|id={{ProQuest|272433825}}}} (Registration required)</ref>

2005年，来自70多个国家的428,856人签署了敞开的门的全球信仰权请愿书，对宗教自由说“是”，对联合国诽谤宗教决议说“不”。<ref>{{cite book|last=Marking|first=J. G.|title=A Voice Is Calling: Living the Life You Know Exists|publisher=A Voice Is Calling|year=2005|pages=117|isbn=1-933204-07-9|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lx-Rj0TzLLwC&pg=PA117&dq=open+doors+brother+andrew|accessdate=2009-04-06}}</ref>请愿书于2010年12月在纽约提交给联合国。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.opendoorsusa.org/take-action/pray/open-doors-global-petition-presented-at-un/|title=Open Doors' Global Petition Presented at United Nations - Open Doors USA|date=2010-12-09|work=Open Doors USA|access-date=2018-04-20|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308130934/https://www.opendoorsusa.org/take-action/pray/open-doors-global-petition-presented-at-un/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2015年，敞开的门及其分支机构在全球分发了300万圣经和相关作品，为239,164人提供了救济和援助。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.opendoorsusa.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/annual_2016_final.pdf|title=Open Doors USA 2015 annual report|publisher=Open Doors USA|accessdate=2018-03-27|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308124102/https://www.opendoorsusa.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/annual_2016_final.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>2018年，美国组织在受迫害教会项目上花费19,291,134美元，其中470万美元用于筹款，280万美元用于行政管理。<ref>Open Doors USA 2018 annual report. 
